# @haku Agent Rules

## Session & context

- **One task = one new chat** — do not continue unrelated work in a long old session.
- **Do not load the whole repo.** Grep → read **3–10 files** relevant to the task.
- Define **done criteria** before coding. Full workflow: `docs/agent-workflow.md`.

## Documentation (pick 1–3 by task, not all)

| Task | Read |
| ---- | ---- |
| Any new task | `docs/agent-workflow.md` |
| Versions / deps | `docs/techstack.md` |
| Architecture / data flow | `docs/architecture.md` |
| Errors / empty states | `docs/edge-cases.md` |
| Editor UI | `docs/ui-kit.md` |
| API / official lib URLs | `docs/links.md` |
| Locked decisions | `IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md` §2 only |

Index: `docs/README.md` · Short map: `AGENTS.md`

**Do not invent `@haku/*` APIs** — check `docs/links.md` § Internal API, then source `index.ts`.

## Package boundaries

- `@haku/engine` / `apps/playground`: **no** React, **no** `@haku/editor`
- `@haku/core` / `@haku/schema`: **no** Three.js
- Component data in `IWorld` only — Three.js via `RenderSyncSystem`, never in components
- Editor mutations: **`commitSceneEdit`** (not direct store writes)
- Entity IDs: UUID v4 · rotation in JSON: quaternion `[x,y,z,w]`

## Editor UI

- Reuse components from `docs/ui-kit.md` (`NumberField`, `InspectorComponentSection`, …)
- **Forbidden:** MUI, Tailwind, R3F, custom number inputs, new UI package outside `packages/editor/`
- Preview: `pnpm --filter @haku/editor-app dev` (no Storybook)

## Implementation & tests

- Incremental slices: schema → serializer → engine → editor (`docs/architecture.md`)
- Test **failure paths**, not happy path only (`docs/edge-cases.md`)
- Verify: `pnpm test`, `pnpm build`; CI-style: `./scripts/check.sh`

## Commits

Only when the user explicitly asks. Format: short first line + summary paragraph. No Co-authored-by Cursor.
